    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"long_descriptions_container\"></div></div><div class=\"qti-layout-row\"> <div class=\"qti-layout-col12\"> <div class=\"prompt\"> <div class=\"standalone_image qti-align-center\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a state transition diagram with two states. Refer to long description.\" aria-describedby=\"LDC-XNV000001_01\" src=\"/images/66fc3d89eef5daa669af2089bd55319b.svg\"><div aria-label=\"Long description for state transition diagram\" class=\"sr-only qti-visually-hidden\" id=\"LDC-XNV000001_01\" role=\"region\"><ul>\n<li class=\"dap_body\">The diagram shows two states, labeled 1 and 2.</li>\n<li class=\"dap_body\">A loop from state 1 pointing back to state 1 is labeled 0.2.</li>\n<li class=\"dap_body\">An arrow from state 1 to state 2 is labeled 0.8.</li>\n<li class=\"dap_body\">A loop from state 2 pointing back to state 2 is labeled 0.9.</li>\n<li class=\"dap_body\">An arrow from state 2 to state 1 is labeled 0.1.</li>\n</ul></div></div><p class=\"dap_body\">Objects in a system can be in two possible states: state&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\"><mn>1</mn></math></span>&nbsp;and state&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\"><mn>2</mn></math></span>. The state transition diagram for this situation is shown. The diagram indicates that&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"20 percent sign\"><math alttext=\"20 percent sign\"><mn>20</mn><mo>%</mo></math></span>&nbsp;of objects in state&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\"><mn>1</mn></math></span>&nbsp;remain in state&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\"><mn>1</mn></math></span>&nbsp;between stages and that&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"90 percent sign\"><math alttext=\"90 percent sign\"><mn>90</mn><mo>%</mo></math></span>&nbsp;of objects in state&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\"><mn>2</mn></math></span>&nbsp;remain in state&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\"><mn>2</mn></math></span>&nbsp;between stages. The constant&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"a subscript i\"><math alttext=\"a subscript i\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></math></span>&nbsp;gives the percent of objects in state&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\"><mn>1</mn></math></span>&nbsp;at stage&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"i\"><math alttext=\"i\"><mi>i</mi></math></span>. The constant&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"b subscript i\"><math alttext=\"b subscript i\"><msub><mi>b</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></math></span>&nbsp;gives the percent of objects in state&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\"><mn>2</mn></math></span>&nbsp;at stage&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"i\"><math alttext=\"i\"><mi>i</mi></math></span>. Matrix&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"M\"><math alttext=\"M\"><mi>M</mi></math></span>&nbsp;is a&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"2 by 2\"><math alttext=\"2 by 2\"><mn>2</mn><mo>Ã—</mo><mn>2</mn></math></span>&nbsp;transition matrix that is used to model objects transitioning between states such that&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"M times a 2 by 1 matrix with row 1 column 1 value a subscript n, row 2 column 1 value b subscript n end matrix equals a 2 by 1 matrix with row 1 column 1 value a subscript n plus 1 end subscript, row 2 column 1 value b subscript n plus 1 end subscript end matrix\"><math alttext=\"M times a 2 by 1 matrix with row 1 column 1 value a subscript n, row 2 column 1 value b subscript n end matrix equals a 2 by 1 matrix with row 1 column 1 value a subscript n plus 1 end subscript, row 2 column 1 value b subscript n plus 1 end subscript end matrix\"><mi>M</mi><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mtable><mtr><mtd><msub><mi>a</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><msub><mi>b</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mtable><mtr><mtd><msub><mi>a</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><msub><mi>b</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math></span>.&nbsp;Which of the following defines&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"M\"><math alttext=\"M\"><mi>M</mi></math></span>&nbsp;?</p> </div> </div> </div>\n",
